# **06  Gesture specification (v1.2 — BREAKING CHANGE)**

**Long-press completely removed. **Every action now has a visible, discoverable entry point. Swipe-reveal is native to iOS and Android — users already know it from Mail, Gmail, WhatsApp without instruction.

| **Gesture** | **How triggered** | **Action** | **Why this is better** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Tap card body** | Single tap on card (not icon area) | Open Meal Detail (H-02) | Obvious. Works from day 1. |
| **Tap swap icon** | Tap refresh/swap icon in action bar | Open carousel (H-03) with 8 alternatives | Icon is always visible. Label shown for first 3 uses. |
| **Swipe left on card** | 40px leftward displacement | Reveal Not Today (amber) + Never (red) buttons | Platform-native. User already knows this from Mail and Gmail. |
| **Tap Not Today button** | After swipe-reveal | Open H-06 confirmation sheet | Visible button. Amber + clock icon. 48px touch target. |
| **Tap Never button** | After swipe-reveal | Open H-07 confirmation sheet | Visible button. Red + trash icon. 48px touch target. |
| **Tap anywhere else** | After swipe-reveal | Cancel: card snaps back | Standard dismiss behaviour. |
| **Tap lock icon** | Single tap on lock in action bar | Lock / unlock slot | Always visible. Fills green when locked. |
| **Tap plus icon** | Single tap on + in action bar | Add to different date (H-08) | Always visible. |
| **Pull down on screen** | Standard pull-to-refresh | Refresh unlocked slots only | Native. Locked slots unchanged. |

| **What changed and why: **Long-press requires users to discover an invisible gesture, hold for exactly the right duration, and then drag in a specific direction. Three sequential discoveries with zero visual affordance. The swipe-reveal pattern requires one discoverable gesture (swipe left, which is standard) and then presents visible, labelled buttons. The barrier to action drops from three steps to two — and both steps are standard platform patterns. |
